### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

compiler-cli, compiler, upgrade

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Hi - I am using angular 12 and now trying to upgrade to version 13 after updating to version 13 (https://update.angular.io/?v=12.0-13.0) when I am building my app it's throwing error with below message.
An unhandled exception occurred: Class extends value undefined is not a constructor or null
See "C:\Users\z004dsas\AppData\Local\Temp\ng-7yn8fy\angular-errors.log" for further details.


